{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":682,"text":"I want to tell you\nabout the future of money."},{"time":4467,"text":"Let's start with a story\nabout this culture"},{"time":7088,"text":"that lived in Micronesia\nin the early 1900s, called the Yap."},{"time":11300,"text":"Now, I want to tell you about the Yap"},{"time":13107,"text":"because their form of money\nis really interesting."},{"time":15997,"text":"They use these limestone discs\ncalled Rai stones."},{"time":19659,"text":"Now, the Yap don't actually\nmove these Rai stones around"},{"time":23410,"text":"or exchange them the way\nwe do with our coins,"},{"time":26231,"text":"because Rai stones can get\nto be pretty massive."},{"time":29720,"text":"The largest is about four tons\nand 12 feet across."},{"time":34072,"text":"So the Yap just keep track\nof who owns part of what stone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40051,"text":"There's a story about these sailors"},{"time":42162,"text":"that were transporting a stone\nacross the ocean"},{"time":44842,"text":"when they ran into some trouble\nand the stone actually fell in."},{"time":49574,"text":"The sailors got back to the main island"},{"time":51920,"text":"and they told everyone what had happened."},{"time":54201,"text":"And everyone decided that, actually, yes,"},{"time":56974,"text":"the sailors had the stone\nand -- why not? -- it still counted."},{"time":61372,"text":"Even though it was\nat the bottom of the ocean,"},{"time":63590,"text":"it was still part of the Yap economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66573,"text":"You might think that this\nwas just a small culture"},{"time":69766,"text":"a hundred years ago."},{"time":71158,"text":"But things like this happen\nin the Western world as well,"},{"time":74330,"text":"and the Yap actually still use\na form of these stones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78360,"text":"In 1932, the Bank of France\nasked the United States"},{"time":82812,"text":"to convert their holdings\nfrom dollars into gold."},{"time":86749,"text":"But it was too inconvenient\nto think about actually shipping"},{"time":90118,"text":"all of that gold over to Europe."},{"time":92071,"text":"So instead, someone went to where\nthat gold was being stored"},{"time":95928,"text":"and they just labeled it\nas belonging to France now."},{"time":100006,"text":"And everyone agreed\nthat France owned the gold."},{"time":103843,"text":"It's just like those Rai stones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106517,"text":"The point I want to make\nwith these two examples"},{"time":108862,"text":"is that there's nothing\ninherently valuable"},{"time":112274,"text":"about a dollar or a stone or a coin."},{"time":116090,"text":"The only reason these things\nhave any value"},{"time":118806,"text":"is because we've all decided they should."},{"time":121398,"text":"And because we've decided that,"},{"time":123251,"text":"they do."},{"time":125223,"text":"Money is about the exchanges\nand the transactions"},{"time":129387,"text":"that we have with each other."},{"time":132042,"text":"Money isn't anything objective."},{"time":134874,"text":"It's about a collective story\nthat we tell each other about value."},{"time":140101,"text":"A collective fiction."},{"time":142170,"text":"And that's a really powerful concept."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146059,"text":"In the past two decades,"},{"time":147550,"text":"we've begun to use digital money."},{"time":149843,"text":"So I get paid via direct deposit,"},{"time":152540,"text":"I pay my rent via bank transfer,"},{"time":155047,"text":"I pay my taxes online."},{"time":157015,"text":"And every month,"},{"time":158191,"text":"a small amount of money\nis deducted from my paycheck"},{"time":160980,"text":"and invested in mutual funds\nin my retirement account."},{"time":165120,"text":"All of these interactions"},{"time":166653,"text":"are literally just changing\n1's and 0's on computers."},{"time":170735,"text":"There's not even anything physical,\nlike a stone or a coin."},{"time":176320,"text":"Digital money makes it\nso that I can pay someone around the world"},{"time":179627,"text":"in seconds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181901,"text":"Now when this works,"},{"time":183516,"text":"it's because there are large institutions\nunderwriting every 1 or 0"},{"time":188385,"text":"that changes on a computer."},{"time":190338,"text":"And when it doesn't,"},{"time":191527,"text":"it's often the fault\nof those large institutions."},{"time":193949,"text":"Or at least, it's up to them\nto fix the problem."},{"time":196916,"text":"And a lot of times, they don't."},{"time":198862,"text":"There's a lot of friction in the system."},{"time":201938,"text":"How long did it take\nthe US credit card companies"},{"time":204837,"text":"to implement chip and pin?"},{"time":206908,"text":"Half my credit cards\nstill don't work in Europe."},{"time":210739,"text":"That's friction."},{"time":212580,"text":"Transferring money across borders\nand across currencies"},{"time":216496,"text":"is really expensive:"},{"time":218807,"text":"friction."},{"time":220292,"text":"An entrepreneur in India\ncan set up an online business in minutes,"},{"time":225239,"text":"but it's hard for her\nto get loans and to get paid:"},{"time":229512,"text":"friction."},{"time":231701,"text":"Our access to digital money\nand our ability to freely transact"},{"time":236569,"text":"is being held captive\nby these gatekeepers."},{"time":239536,"text":"And there's a lot of impediments\nin the system slowing things down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244498,"text":"That's because digital money\nisn't really mine,"},{"time":248064,"text":"it's entries in databases\nthat belong to my bank,"},{"time":251662,"text":"my credit card company\nor my investment firm."},{"time":254839,"text":"And these companies\nhave the right to say \"no.\""},{"time":258856,"text":"If I'm a PayPal merchant"},{"time":260672,"text":"and PayPal wrongly flags me for fraud,"},{"time":265167,"text":"that's it."},{"time":266347,"text":"My account gets frozen,\nand I can't get paid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272789,"text":"These institutions are standing\nin the way of innovation."},{"time":277946,"text":"How many of you use\nFacebook photos, Google Photos,"},{"time":282370,"text":"Instagram?"},{"time":283977,"text":"My photos are everywhere."},{"time":286347,"text":"They are on my phone,\nthey're on my laptop,"},{"time":288856,"text":"they're on my old phone,\nthey're in Dropbox."},{"time":291396,"text":"They're on all these different\nwebsites and services."},{"time":294252,"text":"And most of these services\ndon't work together."},{"time":298816,"text":"They don't inter-operate."},{"time":301538,"text":"And as a result,"},{"time":303055,"text":"my photo library is a mess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306469,"text":"The same thing happens"},{"time":308235,"text":"when institutions control\nthe money supply."},{"time":311962,"text":"A lot of these services\ndon't inter-operate,"},{"time":314721,"text":"and as a result, this blocks\nwhat we can do with payment."},{"time":318185,"text":"And it makes transaction costs go up."},{"time":321723,"text":"So far, we've been through\ntwo phases of money."},{"time":325952,"text":"In an analog world, we had\nto deal with these physical objects,"},{"time":329940,"text":"and money moved at a certain speed --\nthe speed of humans."},{"time":334896,"text":"In a digital world, money can reach\nmuch farther and is much faster,"},{"time":339789,"text":"but we're at the mercy\nof these gatekeeper institutions."},{"time":343222,"text":"Money only moves at the speed of banks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348008,"text":"We're about to enter a new phase of money."},{"time":351158,"text":"The future of money is programmable."},{"time":355034,"text":"When we combine software and currency,"},{"time":358485,"text":"money becomes more\nthan just a static unit of value,"},{"time":362286,"text":"and we don't have to rely\non institutions for security."},{"time":366176,"text":"In a programmable world,"},{"time":367729,"text":"we remove humans\nand institutions from the loop."},{"time":372610,"text":"And when this happens,"},{"time":373993,"text":"we won't even feel like\nwe're transacting anymore."},{"time":377683,"text":"Money will be directed by software,"},{"time":379981,"text":"and it will just safely and securely flow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384828,"text":"Cryptocurrencies are the first step\nof this evolution."},{"time":388787,"text":"Cryptocurrencies are digital money"},{"time":390466,"text":"that isn't run by any government or bank."},{"time":393358,"text":"It's money designed to work\nin a world without intermediaries."},{"time":398153,"text":"Bitcoin is the most ubiquitous\ncryptocurrency,"},{"time":401210,"text":"but there are hundreds of them."},{"time":402931,"text":"There's Ethereum, Litecoin,\nStellar, Dogecoin,"},{"time":406432,"text":"and those are just a few\nof the more popular ones."},{"time":409408,"text":"And these things are real money."},{"time":412507,"text":"The sushi restaurant down my street"},{"time":414386,"text":"takes Bitcoin."},{"time":415966,"text":"I have an app on my phone\nthat I can use to buy sashimi."},{"time":421009,"text":"But it's not just for small transactions."},{"time":423453,"text":"In March, there was a transaction\nthat moved around 100,000 bitcoins."},{"time":428719,"text":"That's the equivalent\nof 40 million US dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433445,"text":"Cryptocurrencies are based on\na special field of mathematics"},{"time":437000,"text":"called cryptography."},{"time":439023,"text":"Cryptography is the study\nof how to secure communication,"},{"time":442818,"text":"and it's about two\nreally important things:"},{"time":445541,"text":"masking information so it can\nbe hidden in plain sight,"},{"time":449143,"text":"and verifying a piece\nof information's source."},{"time":453154,"text":"Cryptography underpins\nso many of the systems around us."},{"time":457387,"text":"And it's so powerful that at times"},{"time":459937,"text":"the US government has actually\nclassified it as a weapon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464591,"text":"During World War II,\nbreaking cryptosystems like Enigma"},{"time":469092,"text":"was critical to decoding\nenemy transmissions"},{"time":472420,"text":"and turning the tide of the war."},{"time":475118,"text":"Today, anyone with a modern\nweb browser is running"},{"time":478436,"text":"a pretty sophisticated cryptosystem."},{"time":481030,"text":"It's what we use to secure\nour interactions on the Internet."},{"time":485015,"text":"It's what makes it safe for us\nto type our passwords in"},{"time":488200,"text":"and to send financial\ninformation to websites."},{"time":491322,"text":"So what the banks used to give us --"},{"time":494173,"text":"trustworthy digital money transfer --"},{"time":496417,"text":"we can now get with a clever\napplication of cryptography."},{"time":501202,"text":"And this means that we don't\nhave to rely on the banks anymore"},{"time":504133,"text":"to secure our transactions."},{"time":506248,"text":"We can do it ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508857,"text":"Bitcoin is based on the very same\nidea that the Yap used,"},{"time":513620,"text":"this collective global\nknowledge of transfers."},{"time":517852,"text":"In Bitcoin, I spend\nby transferring Bitcoin,"},{"time":521488,"text":"and I get paid when someone\ntransfers Bitcoin to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526313,"text":"Imagine that we had this magic paper."},{"time":529711,"text":"So the way that this paper works\nis I can give you a sheet of it"},{"time":533323,"text":"and if you write something on it,"},{"time":535077,"text":"it will magically appear\non my piece as well."},{"time":538721,"text":"Let's say we just give everyone this paper"},{"time":541591,"text":"and everyone writes down\nthe transfers that they're doing"},{"time":545443,"text":"in the Bitcoin system."},{"time":547688,"text":"All of these transfers get copied\naround to everyone else's pieces of paper."},{"time":551658,"text":"And I can look at mine"},{"time":553700,"text":"and I'll have a list of all\nof the transfers that are happening"},{"time":557249,"text":"in the entire Bitcoin economy."},{"time":559779,"text":"This is actually what's happening\nwith the Bitcoin blockchain,"},{"time":563365,"text":"which is a list of all\nof the transactions in Bitcoin."},{"time":567185,"text":"Except, it's not done through paper."},{"time":570023,"text":"It's done through computer code,"},{"time":571743,"text":"running on thousands\nof networked computers"},{"time":574430,"text":"around the world."},{"time":577235,"text":"All of these computers\nare collectively confirming"},{"time":581003,"text":"who owns what Bitcoin."},{"time":582911,"text":"So the Bitcoin blockchain\nis core to how Bitcoin works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586348,"text":"But where do bitcoins actually come from?"},{"time":589930,"text":"Well, the code is designed\nto create new Bitcoin"},{"time":593814,"text":"according to a schedule."},{"time":595680,"text":"And the way that it works\nis that to get those Bitcoin,"},{"time":599120,"text":"I have to solve a puzzle --\na random cryptographic puzzle."},{"time":605069,"text":"Imagine that we had 15 dice,"},{"time":607504,"text":"and we were throwing these dice\nover and over again."},{"time":610603,"text":"Whenever the dice come up all sixes,"},{"time":613059,"text":"we say that we win."},{"time":615095,"text":"This is very close to what these computers\nare all actually doing."},{"time":618995,"text":"They're trying over and over again\nto land on the right number."},{"time":622686,"text":"And when they do,"},{"time":624067,"text":"we say that they've solved the puzzle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627559,"text":"The computer that solves the puzzle"},{"time":630023,"text":"publishes its solution\nto the rest of the network"},{"time":632965,"text":"and collects its reward: new bitcoins."},{"time":636750,"text":"And in the act of solving this puzzle,"},{"time":639008,"text":"these computers are actually\nhelping to secure the Bitcoin blockchain"},{"time":643108,"text":"and add to the list of transactions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645866,"text":"There are actually people\nall over the world running this software,"},{"time":651507,"text":"and we call them Bitcoin miners."},{"time":654438,"text":"Anyone can become a Bitcoin miner."},{"time":657626,"text":"You can go download the software right now"},{"time":660441,"text":"and run it in your computer\nand try to collect some bitcoins."},{"time":664400,"text":"I can't say that I would recommend it,"},{"time":666268,"text":"because right now, the puzzle is so hard\nand the network is so powerful,"},{"time":671393,"text":"that if I tried to mine\nBitcoin on my laptop,"},{"time":674346,"text":"I probably wouldn't see any\nfor about two million years."},{"time":678396,"text":"The miners, professional miners,\nuse this special hardware"},{"time":682667,"text":"that's designed to solve\nthe puzzle really fast."},{"time":685976,"text":"Now, the Bitcoin network\nand all of this special hardware,"},{"time":689842,"text":"there are estimates\nthat the amount of energy it uses"},{"time":692901,"text":"is equivalent to that of a small country."},{"time":696252,"text":"So, the first set of cryptocurrencies"},{"time":698776,"text":"are a little bit slow\nand a little bit cumbersome."},{"time":702331,"text":"But the next generation is going\nto be so much better and so much faster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706744,"text":"Cryptocurrencies are the first step"},{"time":709173,"text":"to a world with a global\nprogrammable money."},{"time":713634,"text":"And in a world with programmable money,"},{"time":716431,"text":"I can pay anyone else securely"},{"time":719982,"text":"without having to sign up\nor ask permission,"},{"time":723579,"text":"or do a conversion or worry\nabout my money getting stuck."},{"time":728428,"text":"And I can send money around the world."},{"time":731482,"text":"This is a really amazing thing."},{"time":734231,"text":"It's the idea of permission-less innovation."},{"time":739447,"text":"The Internet caused\nan explosion of innovation,"},{"time":743195,"text":"because it was built upon\nan open architecture."},{"time":747286,"text":"And just like the Internet\nchanged the way we communicate,"},{"time":751104,"text":"programmable money is going\nto change the way we pay,"},{"time":754404,"text":"allocate and decide on value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757716,"text":"So what kind of world\ndoes programmable money create?"},{"time":760238,"text":"Imagine a world where I can\nrent out my healthcare data"},{"time":764478,"text":"to a pharmaceutical company."},{"time":767063,"text":"They can run large-scale data analysis"},{"time":769592,"text":"and provide me with a cryptographic proof"},{"time":771988,"text":"that shows they're only using my data\nin a way that we agreed."},{"time":776138,"text":"And they can pay me\nfor what they find out."},{"time":779529,"text":"Instead of signing up\nfor streaming services"},{"time":782262,"text":"and getting a cable bill,"},{"time":783855,"text":"what if my television analyzed\nmy watching habits"},{"time":786885,"text":"and recommended well-priced content\nthat fit within my budget"},{"time":790581,"text":"that I would enjoy?"},{"time":792604,"text":"Imagine an Internet without ads,"},{"time":795494,"text":"because instead of paying\nwith our attention when we view content,"},{"time":799525,"text":"we just pay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801831,"text":"Interestingly, things like micro-payments"},{"time":804166,"text":"are actually going to change\nthe way security works in our world,"},{"time":807345,"text":"because once we're better able\nto allocate value,"},{"time":810064,"text":"people will use their money\nand their energies"},{"time":813112,"text":"for more constructive things."},{"time":815727,"text":"If it cost a fraction of a cent\nto send an email,"},{"time":818340,"text":"would we still have spam?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":820674,"text":"We're not at this world yet,"},{"time":822901,"text":"but it's coming."},{"time":824382,"text":"Right now, it's like we're in a world\nthat is seeing the first automobile."},{"time":829579,"text":"The first cryptocurrency,\nlike the first car,"},{"time":833533,"text":"is slow and hard to understand\nand hard to use."},{"time":838095,"text":"Digital money,\nlike the horse and carriage,"},{"time":840665,"text":"works pretty well,"},{"time":842219,"text":"and the whole world economy\nis built on it."},{"time":846386,"text":"If you were the first person on your block"},{"time":848484,"text":"to get a car with an internal\ncombustion engine,"},{"time":851279,"text":"your neighbors would probably\nthink you were crazy:"},{"time":854321,"text":"\"Why would you want\nthis large, clunky machine"},{"time":856818,"text":"that breaks down all the time,\nthat lights on fire,"},{"time":859747,"text":"and is still slower than a horse?\""},{"time":862928,"text":"But we all know how that story turns out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866431,"text":"We're entering a new era\nof programmable money."},{"time":870025,"text":"And it's very exciting,\nbut it's also a little bit scary."},{"time":874691,"text":"Cryptocurrencies can be used\nfor illegal transactions,"},{"time":878229,"text":"just like cash is used for crime\nin the world today."},{"time":882497,"text":"When all of our transactions are online,"},{"time":884999,"text":"what does that mean for surveillance --\nwho can see what we do?"},{"time":890115,"text":"Who's advantaged\nin this new world and who isn't?"},{"time":893226,"text":"Will I have to start to pay for things\nthat I didn't have to pay for before?"},{"time":897372,"text":"Will we all become slaves\nto algorithms and utility functions?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":903114,"text":"All new technology comes with trade-offs."},{"time":906012,"text":"The Internet brought us\na lot of ways to waste time."},{"time":910375,"text":"But it also greatly\nincreased productivity."},{"time":913731,"text":"Mobile phones are annoying"},{"time":915261,"text":"because they make me feel\nlike I have to stay connected to work"},{"time":918269,"text":"all the time."},{"time":919448,"text":"But they also help me stay connected\nto friends and family."},{"time":923274,"text":"The new sharing economy\nis going to eliminate some jobs."},{"time":928165,"text":"But it's also going to create\nnew, flexible forms of employment."},{"time":932601,"text":"With programmable money,"},{"time":934551,"text":"we decouple the need\nfor large, trusted institutions"},{"time":939527,"text":"from the architecture of the network."},{"time":942570,"text":"And this pushes innovation in money\nout to the edges, where it belongs."},{"time":948960,"text":"Programmable money democratizes money."},{"time":952461,"text":"And because of this,\nthings are going to change and unfold"},{"time":955243,"text":"in ways that we can't even predict."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958488,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959674,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}